---
source: tests/cli.rs
expression: "help_output(& [\"tools\", \"clean\", \"--help\"])"
---
Remove the tool cache

Deletes the entire managed-tool cache and reports the space freed; tools are re-downloaded on next use. Prompts for confirmation unless --yes is given.

Usage: hpds tools clean [OPTIONS]

Options:
  -v, --verbose
          Show more detail (underlying commands, tool names)

  -y, --yes
          Delete without asking for confirmation

  -q, --quiet
          Suppress all output except errors

      --no-color
          Disable colored output

      --config <PATH>
          Use this config file instead of discovering hpds.toml

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
